    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Installation - Valve Covers</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.4.15" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Valve Covers</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s26504.4.15.1">
            <title>Right Valve Cover</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use air powered tools when installing valve covers.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e3005119" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Valve cover mounting hardware</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve cover as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position valve cover and gasket on rocker arm carrier.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install valve cover mounting bolts.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten all mounting bolts to the
                        <hotlnk document="eges3001_115.xml" xrefid="E30005B">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s26504.4.15.3">
            <title>Left Valve Cover</title>
            <figure id="e3005120" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Valve cover mounting hardware</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Valve cover bolt (9)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Breather bolt, M6 x 43 (6)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the valve cover as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position valve cover and gasket on rocker arm carrier.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install valve cover mounting bolts.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Tighten all bolts to the
                        <hotlnk document="eges3001_115.xml" xrefid="E30005B">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Installing the crankcase vent hose assembly:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>CF series - Install a new O-ring seal onto hose elbow and seat crankcase vent hose
                            assembly into the breather assembly. Add plastic tie straps to secure hose at the breather
                            bracket, air cleaner bracket, and chassis frame.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Stripped chassis - Install a new O-ring seal onto hose elbow and seat crankcase vent hose
                            assembly into the breather assembly. Install bolt (M10 x 16) to anchor tube to back of
                            cylinder head and tighten to the
                            <hotlnk document="eges3001_311.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">Standard Torque</hotlnk>. Add plastic
                            tie straps to secure hose at the breather bracket, and chassis frame.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed for any reason, install lifting eyes on the rear of each rocker arm carrier
                    and one on the left front carrier. Tighten bolts to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_115.xml" xrefid="E30005B">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s26504.4.15.2">
            <title>Breather Cover (if removed)</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four breather cover opening seals onto beather.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the breather onto the valve cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and finger tighten all breather mounting bolts (M6 x 43) .</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten all bolts to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_115.xml" xrefid="E30005B">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>After the left side valve cover has been installed, the following parts can be placed back on
                        the engine.
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>Crankcase vent hose assembly</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Turbocharger air inlet duct</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Tube assembly, filter to left hand cylinder head</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove tools, parts and equipment.</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Reinstall all safety guards, shields and covers after servicing the engine.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Make sure all tools, loose parts, and service equipment are removed from the engine
                        area after all work is done.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
